    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-25T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="500"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/897: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-25T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 25, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>211. Shanghai’s 902, June 25, noon, quoting statement made by Japanese Embassy
                    spokesman to the press in regard to extraterritorial status of Americans and
                    other foreigners in Japanese-occupied territory in China.</p>
                <p>The Department desires that in reference to the statement of the Japanese Embassy
                    spokesman you seek an early occasion to make a further approach to the Japanese
                    Foreign Office along the lines indicated in the Department’s telegram 384,
                    December 30, 3 p.m.<note n="79" xml:id="d500fn79">
                        <ref target="frus1937v04#pg_426">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1937, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p. 426</ref>.</note> Also see your 15,
                    January 10, noon.<note n="80" xml:id="d500fn80">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_228">p. 228</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>When you have made this approach please make report thereon to the Department by
                    telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
